Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "amen" in different forms and positions, with translations in English in parentheses:

1. *Amen*! (Amen!)
2. Molitva se završila s riječima "amen". (The prayer ended with the word "amen".)
3. U crkvi su svi glasno rekli "amen". (In the church, everyone said "amen" loudly.)
4. *Amen* kažemo na kraju molitve. (We say "amen" at the end of the prayer.)
5. Svećenik je rekao "amen" nakon što su svi izrekli molitvu. (The priest said "amen" after everyone recited the prayer.)
6. Nadam se da će se moje molitve uslišiti *amenom*. (I hope my prayers will be answered with an "amen".)
7. Čuo sam *amen* u tišini noći. (I heard an "amen" in the silence of the night.)
8. Pjesma se završila uz *amen*. (The song ended with an "amen".)
9. *Amen* se koristi i u drugim religijama. (The word "amen" is also used in other religions.)
10. Svi su podigli ruke i rekli *amen*. (Everyone raised their hands and said "amen".)